answers.body_markdown:
You need [`addHeader()`][1] instead of [`setHeader()`][2]. The former *adds* a header while the latter *sets* (and thus overrides any old one) a header.
```java
response.addHeader(&quot;Set-Cookie&quot;, cookieString1);
response.addHeader(&quot;Set-Cookie&quot;, cookieString2);
```

The proper way, however, is to use [`setMaxAge()`][3] method of the `Cookie` class (which takes the expire time in seconds) and use [`addCookie()`][4] the usual way.
```java
public static final int TWO_WEEKS_IN_SECONDS = (int) TimeUnit.DAYS.toSeconds(14);

// ...

Cookie cookie1 = new Cookie(&quot;1&quot;,&quot;1&quot;);
cookie1.setMaxAge(TWO_WEEKS_IN_SECONDS);
response.addCookie(cookie1);

Cookie cookie2 = new Cookie(&quot;2&quot;,&quot;2&quot;);
cookie2.setMaxAge(TWO_WEEKS_IN_SECONDS);
response.addCookie(cookie2);
```

  [1]: https://jakarta.ee/specifications/servlet/6.0/apidocs/jakarta.servlet/jakarta/servlet/http/httpservletresponse#addHeader(java.lang.String,java.lang.String)
  [2]: https://jakarta.ee/specifications/servlet/6.0/apidocs/jakarta.servlet/jakarta/servlet/http/httpservletresponse#setHeader(java.lang.String,java.lang.String)
  [3]: https://jakarta.ee/specifications/servlet/6.0/apidocs/jakarta.servlet/jakarta/servlet/http/cookie#setMaxAge(int)
  [4]: https://jakarta.ee/specifications/servlet/6.0/apidocs/jakarta.servlet/jakarta/servlet/http/httpservletresponse#addCookie(jakarta.servlet.http.Cookie)

