@Jonasz&#39;s answer only works if you can mock the method in `getUserEntities()` and `getUser()`. But what if we have logics inside these methods and we still want unittest run through these methods.

My solution is to change behavior for `CompletableFuture.supplyAsync()` from async to sync by using static mock

```
mockStatic(CompletableFuture.class, invoca -&gt; {
    if (invoca.getMethod().getName().equals(&quot;supplyAsync&quot;)) {
        Supplier&lt;?&gt; supplier = invoca.getArgument(0);
        return CompletableFuture.completedFuture(supplier.get());
    }
    return invoca.callRealMethod();
});
```

With this solution, I can run code inside async block and generic it for all `CompletableFuture` types

